{"title":"Where are incumbents still popular?","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/907734662/0/marginalrevolution~Where-are-incumbents-still-popular.html","date":1731352618000,"content":"<p>From my email, here is your Switzerland fact of the day:</p>\r\n<blockquote><p>The media is awash with stories about western countries incumbent parties losing elections in the last two years:</p></blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F11%2F08%2F2024%2Fthe-democrats-join-a-long-list-of-global-parties-wrecked-by-post-pandemic-backlash&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7Cd3ba6ef60143416e4e2d08dd0232d9ff%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638669139632491761%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=Sv2F3s8CT8P8w%2Br2a33wKzFRYBBMisSNKutFsawRIAs%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.semafor.com/article/11/08/2024/the-democrats-join-a-long-list-of-global-parties-wrecked-by-post-pandemic-backlash</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fe8ac09ea-c300-4249-af7d-109003afb893&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7Cd3ba6ef60143416e4e2d08dd0232d9ff%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638669139632516327%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=QRV%2B6qBKbN5RuA2eMGeg2%2F4Ks1OO3X%2BfvQBZMXsF1ng%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ft.com/content/e8ac09ea-c300-4249-af7d-109003afb893</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote><p>The exception no one seems to remember: Switzerland. In the october 2023 election, 3 out of the 4 governing parties increased their vote share. And it wasn’t just parties that are formally in government but effectively act as an opposition: The right wing Swiss People’s Party won. The left wing Social Democrats one. And the moderate Centre party one. The losers: The centre right Liberal Party (in government) and two different green parties (both outside of government).</p>\r\n<p>Possible cause: Low inflation (<a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmarginalrevolution.com%2Fmarginalrevolution%2F2022%2F10%2Fthe-polity-or-is-it-culture-that-is-swiss.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7Cd3ba6ef60143416e4e2d08dd0232d9ff%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638669139632532749%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=H30xVJy9Z1aik8%2Fo6LDQ139zWpJZCJ7jnVqG%2FSOzmgc%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2022/10/the-polity-or-is-it-culture-that-is-swiss.html</a>)?</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>From Johann C.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/11/where-are-incumbents-still-popular.html\">Where are incumbents still popular?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/907734662/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/907734662/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/907734662/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/907734662/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://asse